                    <div align="center">
                      <b><u><font size="4"><br></font></u></b>
                      <div align="left">
                        <b><u><font size="4">Where</font></u></b>
                      </div>
                    </div>To enchant an item you need to get Enchantment Chips equal to or higher than the level of the item you wish to upgrade. You can either kill many monsters until they drop the chip you need or get them from an Enhancement Chip Exchanger. Monsters will only drop Chips equal to or less than their own <span class="diffRemove">level.</span><span class="diffAdd">level,</span> <span class="diffAdd">unless it&#39;s a monster below 32, upon which it&#39;ll drop level 32 chips instead</span> (i.e. a L32 monster can not drop a L40 Chip).<br>
                    <br>
                    You can trade in three already enchanted equips (including gloves and boots) to the Enhancement Chip Exchanger. It&#39;s better to use three items of the same or nearly the same level as it makes it more predictable as to which Chip you will receive back. If the three Chips are the same level then the Chip will be the next tier up (ie. use three L80 equips in the exchanger and you will receive a L84 Enhancement Chip). Using differing levels of equipment in the exchanger will get you a more random <span class="diffRemove">result.</span><span class="diffAdd">result, though often resulting the average level of the equipment used.</span> There are Enhancement Chip Exchangers located in <b><i>City of Auch (I-6)</i></b> and by the <b>entrance to Gigante Beach</b> at Gigante Dock.<i><br>
                    <br></i> You can also obtain Chips by breaking equipment L32 or over at the Upgrade NPC. Upgrading past +4 has a chance of failure. When it fails and the item breaks you will receive a Chip of the same level as the equipment broken (ie. break a L84 Pistol and receive a L84 Enhancement Chip). Sometimes this can be the cheapest way to obtain certain <span class="diffRemove">Chips.</span><span class="diffAdd">Chips, and is quite worth it for certain item levels, such as level 92.</span><br>
                    <div align="center">
                      <b><i><br>
                      <img align="bottom" alt="Enchanting - Wiki of the new world" height="244" src="http://image.wikifoundry.com/image/3/3RAyj3OYI5yXgrqGrLrCOA90100/GW166H244" title="Enchanting - Wiki of the new world" width="166"></i></b>
                    </div><br>
                    Once you have the chip you then bring it to the Enchant girl located <b><i>City of Auch (I-6)</i></b>.<br>
                    <br>
                    <div align="center">
                      <img align="bottom" alt="Enchanting - Wiki of the new world" height="530" src="http://image.wikifoundry.com/image/3/TEsuM8Coc3ApghfBv6hkVA161022/GW178H530" title="Enchanting - Wiki of the new world" width="178"><font size="4"><b><u><br>
                      <br>
                      <img align="bottom" alt="Enchanting - Wiki of the new world" height="222" src="http://image.wikifoundry.com/image/3/mXu7o0rnApsCv02U51FgBg73266/GW354H222" title="Enchanting - Wiki of the new world" width="354"></u></b></font>
                    </div><font size="4"><b><u>What</u></b></font><br>
                    <br>
                    Enchanting can be applied to any item level 32 and above, except uniques. The Chip must be the same or a higher level than the equipment being enchanted.<br>
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    <u><b><font size="4">Result</font></b></u><br>
                    <br>
                    Results can be any normal modifier found on standard magic/rare items. They can range between just one mod and up to five mods. Sometimes the enchantment fails, you do lose any stats pre-existing modifiers on the item and the Chip, but the item is not destroyed. Each time a Chip is used the previous mods on the equipment will be replaces regardless of whether the chip fails or not.<br>
                    <br>
                    <br>
                    The following are possible mods for the specific item types:<br>
                    <br>
                    <u><b>Leather armor / metal armor / robe / coat</b><br></u> Def + 5 - 20<br>
                    Evasion + 5 - 15<br>
                    Movement speed + 5 - 20%<br>
                    HP +5 - 25%<br>
                    DR +1 - 3<br>
                    <br>
                    <b><u>Shield</u></b><br>
                    Def +3 - 5<br>
                    Block +5 - 10<br>
                    DR +1 - 2<br>
                    <br>
                    <b><u>Melee Weapon</u></b><br>
                    +5 - 40% attack<br>
                    +5 - 30% speed<br>
                    +5 - 10 critical<br>
                    +10 - 50 psycho/mental<br>
                    AR +1 - 3<br>
                    <u><b><br>
                    Firearms</b><br></u>+5 - 40% attack<br>
                    +5 - 30% speed<br>
                    +5 - 10 critical<br>
                    +10 - 20 ACC<br>
                    +30 - 50 psycho/mental<br>
                    AR +1 - 3<br>
                    <br>
                    <u><b>Bracelet</b><br></u>+25 - 40% attack<br>
                    +15 - 30% speed<br>
                    SP +15 - 25%<br>
                    +30 - 80 elemental damage<br>
                    AR +1 - 3<br>
                    <br>
                    <b><u>Canon</u></b><br>
                    +25 - 40 attack<br>
                    +15 - 30% speed<br>
                    SP +15 - 25%<br>
                    +30 - 80 psycho/mental<br>
                    AR +1 - 3<br>
                    <br>
                    <b><u>Gloves</u></b><br>
                    +4 - 5 Accuracy<br>
                    +5% Attack Speed<br>
                    +4 - 5 Defense<br>
                    <br>
                    <b><u>Boots</u></b><br>
                    +1 - 4 Evasion<br>
                    +3% Movement Speed<br>
                    +10% Max HP<br>
                    <br>
                    <b><u><font size="4">Suggestions</font></u></b><br>
                    <font size="2"><br></font><font size="4"><font size="3"><font size="3">Take a few plain items (about 20) Upgrade them by doing them in waves (get them all to +4, then all to +5, then all to +6, etc) I&#39;ve done this up to +8. Then take it over and enchant it till you get the mods you want on it.<br>
                    <br>
                    Note: An Enchant Booster from the cash shop may be used to prevent the chance of getting a blank mod on an equip. <span class="diffAdd">The Enchant Booster assures that you&#39;ll get at least 1 mod in your equipment. Depending on your server, using an Enchant Booster will end up saving you more vis in the end, specially when dealing with higher level equipment, such as level 100 items.</span></font><br></font></font>
